        skos:definition               "a human being recognized by law as an individual subject of rights and obligations"@en;
        skos:inScheme                 webuild:;
        skos:note                     "A natural person exists independently of registration, but her/his legal capacity may be restricted (minor, guardianship, incapacity). \n\nA natural person can act\n- in a private capacity or\n- in a professional or economic capacity (sole trader, freelancer, craftsman, farmer)\n\nA natural person does not cease to be a natural person when conducting business. Economic activity does not transform the person into a legal person, but the natural person can then be considered an economic operator."@en , "A natural person exists independently of registration. A natural person may act in a private capacity or in a professional/economic capacity (e.g., sole trader). Acting economically does not transform the person into a legal person; it expresses the economic operator capacity."@en;
        skos:prefLabel                <urn:uuid:d415b619-215c-44cc-b893-cab5df27b067>;
        skos:related                  webuild:concept-94 , webuild:concept-109;
        suomi-meta:creator            "4c00fd3e-ad5d-4ad6-8782-de29597a5d57";
        suomi-meta:modifier           "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8";
        suomi-meta:publicationStatus  <http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT>;
        term:orderedBroader           ( webuild:concept-41 );
        term:orderedNote              ( "A natural person exists independently of registration, but her/his legal capacity may be restricted (minor, guardianship, incapacity). \n\nA natural person can act\n- in a private capacity or\n- in a professional or economic capacity (sole trader, freelancer, craftsman, farmer)\n\nA natural person does not cease to be a natural person when conducting business. Economic activity does not transform the person into a legal person, but the natural person can then be considered an economic operator."@en "A natural person exists independently of registration. A natural person may act in a private capacity or in a professional/economic capacity (e.g., sole trader). Acting economically does not transform the person into a legal person; it expresses the economic operator capacity."@en );
        term:orderedRelated           ( webuild:concept-109 webuild:concept-94 );
        term:orderedSynonym           ( <urn:uuid:1745f367-be49-46e2-912d-52ceb818d72b> <urn:uuid:3a9a7dda-073a-4520-b699-8bdf5534bc23> ) .

webuild:concept-1  rdf:type           skos:Concept;
        dcterms:created               "2021-12-13T13:59:08Z";
        dcterms:modified              "2026-03-03T06:04:55.903Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        <http://purl.org/termed/properties/id>
                "56d706ed-7a7e-4a2f-9640-28282dd65f7f";
        skos:altLabel                 <urn:uuid:1ac1d898-b700-4b96-9ce7-ca5046703b90>;
        skos:broader                  webuild:concept-41;
        skos:changeNote               "alternative definitions:\n\"a structured group of natural persons or legal persons that is formed to achieve specific objectives, operating according to defined roles, rules, and processes\"\n\"a structured group or arrangement with a defined purpose and governance, capable of acting as an actor in processes\"";
        skos:definition               "a structured arrangement of one or more persons (natural or legal) created to pursue objectives, with roles and rules that enable it to act"@en;
        skos:inScheme                 webuild:;
        skos:narrower                 webuild:concept-109;
        skos:note                     "Represents a collection of people organized together into a community or other social, commercial or political structure. The group has some common purpose or reason for existence which goes beyond the set of people belonging to it and can act as an agent. Organizations are often decomposable into hierarchical structures."@en , "Note: an \"organisation\" may or may not have legal personality; \"legal person\" is the “organisation with legal personality” case."@en;
        skos:prefLabel                <urn:uuid:098a4f27-8a45-4d15-bf71-11a1b39ebf8e> , <urn:uuid:4e8fa96a-a06b-403a-9d40-8a9a6895841c> , <urn:uuid:409042a0-9a8c-4f6b-b314-53b686faedef>;
        suomi-meta:creator            "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8";
        suomi-meta:modifier           "5dc030a4-740f-4dde-9548-4e6e797899d8";
        suomi-meta:publicationStatus  <http://uri.suomi.fi/codelist/interoperabilityplatform/interoperabilityplatform_status/code/DRAFT>;
        term:orderedBroader           ( webuild:concept-41 );
        term:orderedNarrower          ( webuild:concept-109 );
        term:orderedNote              ( "Represents a collection of people organized together into a community or other social, commercial or political structure. The group has some common purpose or reason for existence which goes beyond the set of people belonging to it and can act as an agent. Organizations are often decomposable into hierarchical structures."@en "Note: an \"organisation\" may or may not have legal personality; \"legal person\" is the “organisation with legal personality” case."@en );
        term:orderedSynonym           ( <urn:uuid:1ac1d898-b700-4b96-9ce7-ca5046703b90> ) .

webuild:concept-95  rdf:type          skos:Concept;
        dcterms:created               "2025-12-04T12:49:52.073Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        dcterms:modified              "2025-12-04T13:57:17.754Z"^^xsd:dateTime;
        skos:definition               "anything that can be individually identified as existing, such as a person, organisation, object, event or concept"@en;
        skos:inScheme                 webuild:;
